cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the problem of 3D shape parsing, which involves representing complex 3D shapes with parsimonious part-based representations. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including computer vision (cs.CV), graphics (cs.GR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and robotics (cs.RO). Given that the paper proposes a learning-based solution to this problem, it is likely to be relevant to all of these sub-fields. However, since the paper focuses on the use of superquadrics as atomic elements for 3D shape parsing, it is most likely to be classified under cs.CV and cs.GR.
